{
  "title": "IndexedDbKeyValueStore",
  "description": "KeyValueStore over IndexedDB (via IndexedDbStore), using the **structured-clone** algorithm. Unlike WebStorageStore, values are stored *directly* — no `JSON.stringify`. So `Blob`s, `ArrayBuffer`s, typed arrays and nested objects round-trip natively, and there is no string-size ceiling beyond the (large) IndexedDB quota. Use this for binary or large saves; use `WebStorageStore` for small synchronous JSON.",
